Text: "Go to learn at the library: they're free!" - a classic Glen Beck line, classic Tea party logic.

I'm reminded of the scene from "Good Will Hunting" where Matt Damon's character shows up the Harvard student and argues that you can get the same education and only incur a few bucks in late fees at the public library. That scene is an unrealistic view of both intelligence and the wealth of learning that can be gained, unguided, for free.
